Used to dislike butterscotch on recipes except just a very tiny bit of it.. Now i like it much more.&#xD;
This is a simple, good old type of RY4 - D that you normally get but i feel butterscotch adds more layers to RY4D than most caramels or other sweeteners in general.&#xD;
&#xD;
To make a little bit more like cigarrette tobacco  i think i'll add just a tiny bit of tpa werstern maybe around 0.3% but haven't tried it out yet. I do that because i like the little bit of tobacco flavour that ry4d shows at around 3 weeks plus of steeeping, not the same thing but tpa werstern in very small amounts exercebates that flavour at leat to me  it does.
